snippet.textDisplay:
Wilder vs Fury

(First Fight)

R1: 10/9 DW
R2: 10/9 DW
R3: 9/10 TF
R4: 10/9 DW
R5: 9/10 TF
R6: 10/9 DW
R7: 9/10 TF
R8: 9/10 TF
R9: 10/8 DW
R10: 9/10 TF
R11: 9/10 TF
R12: 10/8 DW

DW: 114
TF: 112

DW was more aggressive in the beginning rounds, with nice accurate jabs, and decent rights. He slowed down in the middle rounds, missed more, and over expended his energy, got sloppy and therefore got caught by TF quick counter attacks. DW acknowledged he needed to do something big to turn the tide, and gets a knockdown, TF gets up to make a short comeback but not enough, round 8 remains a 10/8 for DW. DW clearly over exerted himself in round 8, allowing TF to tee off on him for parts of the next two rounds, but DW was never in any real trouble. DW goes for broke in R12, and the gamble pays off, scores huge classy ko. TF shows tremendous tenacity to get up, DW goes for the kill, but TF had enough on the tank to see the round through. In conclusion; TF got some nice combos in on DW, unfortunately TF never really rocked DW. TF made DW look bad at times, by making him miss haymakmers, but you don't get points for that. In the end DW, was more aggressive and landed the bigger, harder shots, that got him not one, but two knockdowns, which were the difference makers in the fight. DW deserved the win, because he was less conservative, took greater risks, was more aggressive and landed the bigger shots that led to multiple knockdowns.
